<taxonomicName id="2B8C4D5CFFA0FF9DFF21DAB8FE1A78B1" authority="Melichar" authorityName="Melichar" box="[151,484,666,689]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Dussana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quaerenda">
<emphasis id="DEF8EACDFFA0FF9DFF21DAB8FE8C78B1" box="[151,370,666,689]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="57">Dussana quaerenda</emphasis>
Melichar
</taxonomicName>
: 
<treatmentCitation id="6D2D10CEFFA0FF9DFE45DAB8FD3178B1" author="Pruthi, H. S." box="[499,719,666,689]" page="85" pageId="6" pageNumber="57" year="1934">
<bibRefCitation id="881D4B2EFFA0FF9DFE45DAB8FD3178B1" author="Pruthi, H. S." box="[499,719,666,689]" pageId="6" pageNumber="57" pagination="69 - 99" refId="ref4584" refString="Pruthi, H. S. 1934. Studies on Indian Jassidae (Homoptera). Part II. Description of the genotypes of some of the genera founded by W. L. Distant, with a revision of the genus Moonia Distant. Memoirs of the Indian Museum, 11, 69 - 99." type="journal article" year="1934">Pruthi 1934: 85–86</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
, text fig. 104 a–c, Plate 7, figs 2, 2a, misidentification; 
<treatmentCitation id="6D2D10CEFFA0FF9DFAD4DAB8FE9C78D1" author="Datta, B." page="107" pageId="6" pageNumber="57" year="1972">
<bibRefCitation id="881D4B2EFFA0FF9DFAD4DAB8FE9C78D1" author="Datta, B." pageId="6" pageNumber="57" pagination="102 - 108" refId="ref4313" refString="Datta, B. 1972. On Indian Cicadellidae (Homoptera) - VI. Zoologischer Anzeinger, Leipzig, 189, 102 - 108." type="journal article" year="1972">Datta 1972:107–108</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
, Plate 5, A–D (in part), misidentification; 
<treatmentCitation id="6D2D10CEFFA0FF9DFC90DA98FC3978D1" author="Datta, B." box="[806,967,698,721]" page="52" pageId="6" pageNumber="57" year="1988">
<bibRefCitation id="881D4B2EFFA0FF9DFC90DA98FC3978D1" author="Datta, B." box="[806,967,698,721]" pageId="6" pageNumber="57" refId="ref4339" refString="Datta, B. 1988. On Oriental Cicadellidae (Homoptera: Insecta). Miscellaneous Publication, Occasional Paper No. 90, xiv + 256 pp. Records of the Zoological Survey of India." type="book" year="1988">Datta 1988: 52</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
, Figs 91–94, (in part), misidentification.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EC3336DFFFA0FF9DFF21DB20FDA27994" blockId="6.[151,1436,770,1636]" pageId="6" pageNumber="57">
Colouration similar to 
<taxonomicName id="2B8C4D5CFFA0FF9DFE1FDB20FDB5791B" authorityName="Viraktamath &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2007" box="[425,587,770,795]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pythamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bispinosus">
<emphasis id="DEF8EACDFFA0FF9DFE1FDB20FDB5791B" box="[425,587,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="57">D. bispinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but hyaline spot on forewing much narrower, not exceeding subcostal cell and scutellum more broadly whitish near apex. In some females apices of outer claval veins, clavus and irregular area between claval apex and apex of hyaline costal triangle, brownish. Abdominal pleura yellow, sterna brown, genital segments brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A4966554FFA0FF9DFF71DB80FE747EFC" pageId="6" pageNumber="57" type="description">
<paragraph id="EC3336DFFFA0FF9DFF71DB80FE107E34" blockId="6.[151,1436,770,1636]" pageId="6" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis id="DEF8EACDFFA0FF9DFF71DB80FE8C79BB" box="[199,370,930,955]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="57">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: Process of the ventro-cephalic angle of tenth segment short. Pygophore rounded caudally, ventral process rather S-shaped, distal 0.33 with wavy ridge. Stem of connective three times as long as arms. Aedeagus constricted at base, with a pair of short processes near base, their length not exceeding minimum width of shaft in lateral view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EC3336DFFFA0FF9DFF71DC61FE617E84" blockId="6.[151,1436,770,1636]" pageId="6" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis id="DEF8EACDFFA0FF9DFF71DC61FE6F7E5C" box="[199,401,1091,1116]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="57">Female genitalia</emphasis>
: Seventh sternum three times as wide as long, hind margin slightly broadly produced and bilobed in middle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EC3336DFFFA0FF9DFF71DCB0FE747EFC" blockId="6.[151,1436,770,1636]" pageId="6" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis id="DEF8EACDFFA0FF9DFF71DCB0FE767EAC" bold="true" box="[199,392,1170,1196]" pageId="6" pageNumber="57">Measurements:</emphasis>
Male 
<quantity id="2B749B3AFFA0FF9DFE62DCB0FD9E7EAC" box="[468,608,1170,1196]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.15" metricValueMax="6.4" metricValueMin="5.9" pageId="6" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="6.15" valueMax="6.4" valueMin="5.9">5.9–6.4 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="2B749B3AFFA0FF9DFD1ADCB0FCC77EAC" box="[684,825,1170,1196]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="6" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="1.15" valueMax="1.2" valueMin="1.1">1.1–1.2 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes and 
<quantity id="2B749B3AFFA0FF9DFBF7DCB0FB337EAC" box="[1089,1229,1170,1196]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="6" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="1.35" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.3">1.3–1.4 mm</quantity>
wide across hind margin of pronotum. Female 
<quantity id="2B749B3AFFA0FF9DFE40DC98FD7B7ED4" box="[502,645,1210,1236]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.05" metricValueMax="7.3" metricValueMin="6.8" pageId="6" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="7.05" valueMax="7.3" valueMin="6.8">6.8–7.3 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="2B749B3AFFA0FF9DFD64DC98FCD07ED4" box="[722,814,1210,1236]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="6" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes and 
<quantity id="2B749B3AFFA0FF9DFB8ADC98FB357ED4" box="[1084,1227,1210,1236]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="6" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="1.45" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.4">1.4–1.5 mm</quantity>
wide across hind margin of pronotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
